src: laʁjɯɣ nɤʑo tɤ-nɯ-ndɤm je
trs: Take the staff.' (2005 khu, 13)

src: nɤʑo nɤkinɯ, tɤ-tɯ-nɯrdoʁ, aj tɤ-nɯ-ndo-t-a me
trs: It is you who collected (the fruits), I did not take them.' (lWlu 2002, 51)

src: nɯnɯ ɯ-ʁrɯ nɯnɯ tʰɯ-rgɤz tɕe tɕe nɯ ɯʑo pjɯ-ɤ<nɯ>tɤr ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: When its antlers age, they fall off by themselves.' (27-qartshAz, 35)

src: tɕe ji-kɤ-nɯ-raχtɕɤz ra jɤ-ɣe-nɯ, iʑora tu-nɯ-ʑɣɤ-raχtɕɤz-i,
trs: When people we cherish come, or when we (wish) to treat ourselves,' (30 macha, 74)

src: tu-tɯ́-wɣ-ndza ɯ-ɲɯ-sɯsɤm qʰe a-tɤ-tɯ́-wɣ-nɯ-ndza ɲɯ-ntsʰi
trs: If it wants to eat you, let it eat you!'  (150901 dongguo xiansheng he lang-zh, 100)

src: tɤ-tɕɯ nɯnɯ, kɯ, nɯnɯtɕu kɯnɤ pjɤ-n-nɯ-rga ɕti.
trs: Even like that, the boy still loved her.' (140510 sanpian sheye-zh, 121)

src: nɤ-ku pɯ-nɯ-χtɕi
trs: Wash your head.' (elicited)

src: ɯʑo kɯ ɯ-sroʁ ko-nɯ-ri ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: He saved his own life.' (140512 yufu yu mogui-zh, 127)

src: tɯ-ci ɯ-ŋgɯ ɯ-ʁrɯm pjɯ-kɯ-ntɕʰɤr nɯ pjɤ-nɯ-mto tɕe,
trs: She saw her (own) reflection in the water.' (140428 mu e guniang-zh, 59)

src: tɯrpa ci to-lɤt ri, si nɯ ɯ-taʁ mɯ-to-xtsɯɣ kɯ ɯʑo ɣɯ ɯ-jaʁ ʑo to-nɯ-xtsɯɣ.
trs: He swung the axe but did not hit the tree, and instead hit his own arm.' (140430 jin e-zh, 41)

src: kɤtsa ra χsɯm nɯ kɯ-scɯ\redp{}scit ʑo ku-nɯ-rɤʑi-nɯ pjɤ-ŋu,
trs: The three of them lived happily.' (Gesar 2003, 211)

src: tɕiʑo ʁnɯz ma maŋe-tɕi tɕe, ʑaka kɤ-nɯ-βzu mɤ-rtaʁ-tɕi
trs: We are only two, we are not enough people to act separately.' (The three sisters, 74)

src: [``aʑɯɣ a-pɯ-nɯ-pe" ɲɯ-kɯ-sɯso] ci pjɤ-ŋu
trs: He was someone who was (always) thinking `May it be beneficial to me!'' (140430 jin e-zh, 31)

src: nɤʑo nɯnɯtɕu kɤndza kɯ-mɯm ɕ-tɤ-nɯ-ndze
trs: Go and eat nice food there!' (140426 jiagou he lang-zh, 64)

src: a-wɯ a-wi ra kutɕu nɯ-n-nɤʁaʁ-nɯ, a-nɯ-tɯ-nɯ-rɯmani-nɯ, tɕe kutɕu a-kɤ-tɯ-nɯ-rɤʑi-nɯ
trs: Grandfathers and grandmothers, have a good time here, recite mantras and stay here (pleasantly).' (2003kandzwsqhaj, 61)

src: tɕe zrɯɣ nɯ tɕe, tsuku kɯ tɯ-pɤcʰaʁ ɯ-ŋgɯ tu-nɯ-ɬoʁ ŋu tu-ti-nɯ ŋu tɕe mɤ-xsi ma ɯʑo ɲɯ-kɯ-nɯ-βze ci ɲɯ-ɕti tɕe,
trs: The louse, some say that it comes from the navel, I don't know, it grows by itself.' (21 mdzadi, 61)

src: si ɯ-rgɤm nɯ ɣɯ ɯ-fkaβ nɯ, ɯʑo to-nɯ-ɲɟɯ.
trs: The cover of the box opened by itself.' (150906 toutao-zh, 180)

src: aʑo pjɯ-kɯ-nɯ-βde-a-nɯ mɤ-ra, aʑo pjɯ-nɯ-mtsaʁ-a jɤɣ
trs: You don't need to throw me in there, I will jump by myself (of my own free will).' (2011-05-nyima, 152)

src: aʑo ʑo z-ɲɯ-nɯ-ru-a ɲɯ-ntsʰi
trs: I need to go and have a look by myself.' (140507 tangguowu-zh, 141)

src: kʰɯtsa pɯ-qrɯ-t-a
trs: I broke the bowl (possibly on purpose).' (elicited)

src: kʰɯtsa pɯ-nɯ-qrɯ-t-a
trs: I broke the bowl (by mistake).' (elicited)

src: hehe a-ʑi ra cʰɤ-tɯ-nɯ-rɤrɟit-nɯ mɯ́j-tɯ-nɯ-sɯχsɤl-nɯ
trs: My lady, you had a child and did not notice it.' (2003 Kunbzang, 118)

src: mɤ-xsi ko, nɯra ɲɤ-nɯ-jmɯt-a
trs: I don't know, I forgot those things.' (Conversation, 2013-12-24)

src: ``huaguniang" ra tu-nɯ-ti-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋu. nɯnɯra ʑara kɯ ɯ-rmi tu-nɯ-tɕɤt-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: They say `huaguniang', they call (this type of cows) like that.' (\textit{implied meaning}: they invented their name, it is not a real name; 28 qapar, 239)

src: tɕe tɯ-sɯm pɯ-a<nnɯ>ri nɤ ju-kɯ-ɕe, mɯ-pɯ-a<nnɯ>ri nɤ ju-kɯ-ɕe pɯ-ra
trs: Whether one liked it or not, one had to go.' (14 tApi taRi, 212)

src: nɯ li ɯ-qa ɲɯ-βze ɲɯ-ɕti ma ɯ-mɯntoʁ pɯ-nnɯ-tu kɯnɤ, ɯ-rɣi ra kɤ-mto maŋe.
trs: This one also grows by its root, as even if it has flowers, (I) have never seen its seeds.' (17 ndZWnW, 155)

src: nɤʑo nɯ-nɯ-ɣɤwu ma, nɤ-kɯ-nɯɣ-mu me ma mɤ-ta-mbi
trs: You can cry as much as you like, nobody is afraid of you, I won't give (my daughter) to you (in marriage).' (2002 qaCpa, 149)

imt: crow \textsc{erg} what \textsc{neg}-\textsc{auto}-say:\textsc{fact} be.\textsc{aff}:\textsc{fact} \textsc{sfp} \textsc{irr}-\textsc{pfv}-\textsc{auto}-say \textsc{lnk} be:\textsc{fact} not.even not.be:\textsc{fact} \textsc{sfp}
src: qajdo kɯ tɕʰi mɤ-nɯ-ti ɕti nɤ, a-tɤ-nɯ-ti ma ŋu cinɤ maʁ kɯ,
trs: The crow says all kinds of things, let it say (whatever it likes), in any case none of it is true.'  (28-qAjdoskAt, 27)

src: tɕʰeme nɯ ɲɤ-nɯkʰɤda ri, mɯ-pjɤ-pʰɤn, tɕʰeme nɯ pjɤ-nɯ-ɣɤwu ɕti,
trs: She (tried to) comfort the girl, but it was for nothing, the girl kept on crying.' (zrAntCW 2003 48)

src: nɯnɯ pjɯ-ŋgra ɕɯŋgɯ tɕe tɕe ɲɯ-rom ɕti tɕe, ɯ-rɣi nɯnɯ tɕu a-nɯ-mpʰɯr ɕti
trs: Before (the flower) falls down, it dries up, and its seed is still wrapped in it.' (13 tCamu, 59)

src: tɤtʰo nɯnɯ qartsɯmɤftɕar ʑo a<nɯ>rŋi ɕti
trs: The pine (remains) green the whole year.' (07 tAtho, 51)

src: ʑmbɯlɯm chondɤre grɯβgrɯβ kɯ-fse tɤ-ɬoʁ tɕe χploʁχploʁ kɯ-pa tɕe ʑɯrɯʑɤri ɲɯ-kɯ-nɤwɤt nɯ ɲɯ-maʁ. tɤ-ɬoʁ jɤznɤ ɲɯ-xtɕi laʁma nɯ kɯ-fse ɲɯ-nɯ-ŋɯ\redp{}ŋu qʰe
trs: It is not like the (mushroom called) \forme{ʑmbɯlɯm} and the Matsutake, which are spherical when they come out and progressively open towards the exterior. It is just that it is small when it comes out, (otherwise) it is already like that.'  (24-zwArqhAjmAG, 19)

src: ndi na-ʑa-nɯ qʰe, tɕendi zɯ mɤ-kɯ-βɟɤt ɯ-rca ntsɯ ɲɯ-nɤtɯɣ pjɤ-ŋu.
trs: When they started (distributing food) from the west, he was each time among those who did not get anything.' (28-qAjdoskAt, 157)

src: kɯki kɯ-ɤmtɕoʁ nɯnɯ ɯ-mci pjɯ-kɯ-ɣi ɯ-stu nɯ ɲɯ́-wɣ-z-nɤtɯɣ.
trs: One (turns/puts) the corner (of the bib) towards the direction of the drooling saliva (of the baby).' (vid-20140506043657, 19)

src: ɕɤr tɯtsʰot sqamnɯz ʑo tɕe a-jɤ-tɯ-z-nɤtɯɣ tɕe,
trs: You will have to make sure to be there at midnight.' (2003qachga, 26)

src: jɤ-a<nɯ>ri ri, ɯ-rte ɲɤ-nɯβde
trs: He went away, but lost his hat.' (2010-07-pear story, 21)

src: nɯ kɯ ɯ-rʑaβ a-kɤ-nɯte ɲɯ-ntsʰi
trs: Let him take her as his wife.' (140513 shenqi de feitan-zh, 183

src: nɤ-rɟɤntɕʰa nɯra aʑo ci pjɯ-kɯ-z-nɯta-a tɕe
trs: Can you let me wear your ornaments?' (2014-kWlAG, 472)

src: ɯ-tɤrʁaʁɕa nɯra ɯ-zda ra ɲɯ-z-nɯ-krɤm, ɲɯ-mbi ntsɯ pjɤ-ŋu.
trs: He would share the meat from his hunt with the others, give it to them.' (150902 hailibu-zh, 6)

src: kʰɤdi ʁnɯz-mɯz nɯ-antsɤndu mɤ-nɯ-sɯχsɤl
trs: (Your king) does not realize that two (different sisters) have been exchanged at the lady seating place.' (2003 Kunbzang, 329; see §\ref{sec:orientation.kitchen} on the meaning of \forme{kʰɤdi})

src: nɯʑora ɲɯ-tɯ-ɤntsɤndu-nɯ
trs: You are the opposite way!' (conversation 16-04-12; context: I told Tshendzin that my father and I cannot drive cars, while my mother and my wife can)

src: tɕi-ŋga to-nɯ-sɯ-ɤntsɤndu-tɕi
trs: We exchanged our clothes by mistake.' (elicited)

src: iɕqʰa rɟɤlpu ɯ-tɕɯ nɯ kɯ tɤɕime nɯ, ɯʑo ɯ-rɟɤlkʰɤβ nɯtɕu jo-nɯ-tsɯm qʰe
trs: The prince took the girl back (\textit{vertitive}) to his kingdom.' (140504 baixue gongzhu-zh, 232)

src: aʑɯɣ nɯ-nɯβde-t-a nɯ ɯ́-ŋu tɯ-ci kɯ tʰɯ-a-nɯ-tsɯm nɯ ɯ́-ŋu
trs: Is it the one that I lost? Is it the one that the water took away (\textit{spontaneous})?' (140427 bianfu jingji he shuiniao-zh, 29)

src: tɯ-ɣjɤn pjɯ-ta-z-nɯ-ɕe jɤɣ ri,
trs: I can let you go back home one time.' (150901 changfamei-zh, 171)

src: aʑo kɯnɤ nɯ́-wɣ-mbi-a, mɯ-nɯ-sɯ-ndza-j tɕe tɕendɤre <dong> ntsɯ pɯ-βzu-t-a.
trs: She gave (some edible ferns) to me, we could not eat (all of it), so I froze it.' (conversation140510)

imtwordshtml: 3pl.poss-neg-obj:pcp-abil-eat
src: nɯ-mɤ-kɤ-sɯ-ndza nɯnɯ nɯ-kʰo ɯ-ŋgɯ nɯtɕu ɯ-pɯ tu-nɯ-pa-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋgrɤl,
trs: (The mice gathered food) and would keep in their room (the food) that they are not able to eat.' (150818 muzhi guniang-zh, 291)

src: sɤnɤmmtsʰu kɯ kɤ-ntsɣe cʰɤ-ɣɯt ri mɯ́j-sɯ-ntsɣe ndɤre,
trs: Bsod.nams.mtsho brought them (to Mbarkham) to sell, but could not sell it.' (conversation, 14.05.10)

src: tɕe li nɯ-kɤ-ndza ɲɤ-me qʰe tɕe nɤ li, tɤ-rɟit ra mɤ-sɯ-χsu-ndʑi pjɤ-ɕti qʰe
trs: They ran out of food, and were about to be unable to feed the children.' (160701 poucet2, 55-56)

src: tɕendɤre ɯ-βlu ʑaʑa ʑo mɯ-to-sɯ-tɕɤt tɕe ʑɯmkhɤm ʑo cʰɤ-rɯ-sɯso pjɤ-ra.
trs: He could not find a solution at first, and had to think for a long time.' (140425 ajimide1, 19)

src: a-βlu tɤ-sɯ-tɕa-t-a
trs: I succeeded in finding a solution.' (elicited)

src: tɯrme laʁnɯlaχsɯm kɯnɤ mɤ-kɤ-sɯ-rqoʁ kɯ-fse kɯ-jpum ɲɯ-βze cʰa
trs: (The Fir) can grow so thick that two or three people cannot hug (its trunk).' (08-tWrgi, 6)

src: kɯki taqaβ ki, ɯ-xso taqaβ nɯ maʁ, nɤkinɯ, nɯfse taqaβ nɯ maʁ tɕe, nɯ rcanɯ, tɕʰi nɯ-tɯ-sɯso-t cʰɯ-tɯ-nɯ-sɯ-tʂɯβ kʰɯ
trs: This needle is no ordinary needle, it is not a simple needle like that, (with it) you will be able to sew whatever you like.' (140508 benling gaoqiang de si xiongdi-zh, 103)

src: ɯ-ʁar ra ko-tsʰoʁ-nɯ tɕe tɕendɤre, rɟɤlpu nɯ chonɤ aʁɤndɯndɤt ju-nɯqambɯmbjom-ndʑi tɕe ju-nɤɕɯɕe-ndʑi ra to-khɯ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: They attached wings on her back, and she became able to fly around everywhere with the king.' (150818 muzhi guniang-zh, 515)

src: ko-rɟɯɣ nɤ ɲɤ-rɟɯɣ ʑo qʰe,
trs: She ran around.' (150901 changfamei-zh, 112)

src: ɯʑo-sɯso ju-nɤɕɯɕe mɯ-pjɤ-jɤɣ
trs: (The nightingale) was not allowed to (fly) around freely.' (140519 yeying-zh, 109)

src: tɕendɤre ɲɤ-ɕe nɤ ɲɤ-ɕe tɕe tɕendɤre, tɕendi tɕe tɕe, tɕendi tɕendi tɕe tɕendɤre mtsʰu ci ɲɤ-k-ɤtɯɣ-ci.
trs: He went towards the west (for a long time), very far in the west, and found a lake.' (28-smAnmi, 91-92)

src: ɯ-ɕna ra ɲɤ-nɤɕtʰɯɕtʰɯz tɕeri, nɤki, tɤ-pɤtso ra khri ɯ-pa kɤ-kɤ-sɯ-ɤnbaʁ nɯ pjɤ-sɯχsɤl matɕi ɯ-di pjɤ-mnɤm tɕe,
trs: (The ogre) pointed his nose in all directions, and discovered the children that had been hidden under the bed because of the smell.' (160704 poucet4-v2, 4-5)

src: tɕendɤre ʑɯ\redp{}ʑimkʰɤm ʑo aʁɤndɯndɤt ʑo ɲɤ-nɤtʰɯtʰu tɕe ``qala ŋoj nɯ-ari" ntsɯ to-ti pjɤ-nɤtʰɯtʰu tɕe,
trs: (The bear) asked around everywhere for a very long time where the rabbit had gone.' (2011-13-qala, 21-22)

imtwordshtml: aor-auto-caus-be.hoarse-pst:tr-1sg
src: kɤ-nɤtɯti kɯ a-rqo ʑo kɤ-nɯ-sɯɣ-ndzi-t-a
trs: My voice has become hoarse (I have made my voiced become hoarse) because of speaking again and again.' (elicited)

src: tɕendɤre tɕʰeme nɯ ɕ-to-nɤtsʰɯtsʰɤt ri, tɯ\redp{}ta-nɤtsʰɯtsʰɤt ʑo nɯ tɕʰeme nɯ kɯ laʁnɤlaʁ ʑo tu-ste pɯ-ɕti ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: He has gone and tested the girl again and again, and each time he tested her, she answered correctly with ease.' (2005tAwakWcqraR, 54)

src: pjɯ-nɤsɲɯsɲu ntsɯ pjɤ-ɕti tɕe
trs: He always did (all sorts of) crazy things.' (150829 jidian-zh, 12)

src: tɕʰi ɲɯ-tɯ-nɤme ŋu, tɕʰi ɲɯ-tɯ-nɤfsɯfse ɲɯ-ŋu ma, nɤki jɤ-pʰɣo ma
trs: What are you doing, what kind of foolish act are you doing, flee!' (Norbzang 2012, 65)

src: tɕe ki a-tɤɲi ki lu-nɤkʰɯkʰrɯt-a tɕe aʑo lu-mɤku-a ŋu tɕe, a-qʰu lɤ-ɣi je tɕe, a-tɤɲi ɯ-jrɯ\redp{}jroʁ ʑo lɤ-ɣi je tɕe,
trs: I am going up there first, dragging this staff$_i$ (of mine) along, come after me and follow its$_i$ trace.' (2005 Kunbzang, 200-201)

src: ɯ-mat nɯ ɲɯ-rko tɕe ɲɯ́-wɣ-nɤmɯma tɕe rʁom.
trs: Its fruit is hard and rough to the touch.' (12-ndZiNgri, 44)

src: nɤʑo nɤ-pʰɯpʰɯ kɤ-ɣɯt aj a-ʁa ku-me
trs: I don't have time to give you alms.'(2003kandZislama, 154)

src: ʑara-stɯsti tɕe nɯ-kɯ-nɤstɯstu maŋe,
trs: When alone (without their young ones), (the wild yaks) have no enemies (predators).' (20-RmbroN, 50)

src: kɤntɕʰaʁ ra cʰɤ-z-nɤmɲole
trs: He (took) him to do sightseeing in the city.' (140511 alading-zh, 53)

src: ɯ-mɯntoʁ nɯra aɣrɤɣrum ɯ-ŋgɯz kɯnɤ aqarŋɯrŋe kɯ-fse
trs: Its flower is whitish, with a taint of yellowish.' (`it is like yellowish inside the whitish colour') (16-CWrNgo, 207)

src: tɕeri qro nɯnɯ wuma ʑo wɣrum, kɯ-wɣrɯ\redp{}wɣrum ʑo ŋu.
trs: The pigeon is very white.' (24-qro, 2)

src: ɯ-mɯntoʁ rca wuma ʑo mpɕɤr tɕe kɯ-qarŋɯ\redp{}rŋe ʑo ŋu.
trs: Its flower is very beautiful, it is very yellow.

src: waɟɯ ɲɤ-nmu
trs: There was an earthquake.' (elicited)

src: ma-nɯ-tɯ-mɯnmu ma mɤ-pʰɤn
trs: Don't move, otherwise it won't work!' (2002 qala, 69)

src: tɕe nɯŋa ɯʑo nɯnɯ, sqamŋu-xpa jamar cʰɯ-mdɯ ɲɯ-ŋgrɤl
trs: A cow itself can live up to fifteen years.' (05-qaZo, 142)

imt: \textsc{2sg} \textsc{dem} ten.thousand-year \textsc{irr}-\textsc{pfv}-2-live.up.to be.needed:\textsc{fact} \textsc{sfp} \textsc{ifr}-say \textsc{sens}-be \textsc{lnk} \textsc{1sg} also  ten.thousand-year \textsc{comit} one-day \textsc{dem} \textsc{ipfv}-live.up.to-\textsc{1sg} be.needed:\textsc{fact} \textsc{ifr}-say
src: ``nɤʑo nɯ kʰrɯtsu-xpa a-tʰɯ-tɯ-mdɯ ra nɤ" to-ti ɲɯ-ŋu. tɕe ``aʑo kɯnɤ kʰrɯtsu cʰondɤre tɯ-rʑaʁ nɯnɯ cʰɯ-mdɯ-a ra" to-ti
trs: He said: `May you live ten thousand years! I want to live one thousand years and one more day.' (150830 afanti-zh, 64)

src: aʑo kɯrɯ-skɤt kɤ-βzjoz nɯ cʰɯ-mdɯt-a ʑo ɕti
trs: I am determined to learn Tibetan/Gyalrong.' (elicited)

src: nɯnɯra ɣɯ nɯ-rte nɯ ci ɯ-qʰu ci ʑo to-nɯ-mɟa. to-nɯ-mɟa qʰe jo-tsɯm qʰe ɯ-pi ra tɯkaka nɯ-ku ɯ-taʁ pjɤ-ta.
trs: He took their crowns one after the other and put them on the heads of each of his brothers.' (160705 poucet5-v2, 19-20)

src: tɯ-sŋi kɤ-mdi tu-kɯ-rɤma, <gongfen> ʁnɯ-skɤrma pjɯ́-wɣ-mɟa ma mɯ-pɯ-kɯ-cʰa, pɯ-kɯ-xtɕi.
trs: Working a complete day, I could only get two cents of labour points, as I was young.' (2010-09, 86)

src: kɤ-ndza maka mɯ-pjɤ-βɟɤt.
trs: He did not obtain anything to eat.' (qajdoskAt 2002, 104)

src: tɤ-tɕɯ stu kɯ-wxti nɯnɯ kɯ [nɯnɯ tɕʰeme nɯ mɯ-pɯ-kɤ-βɟɤt] nɯ wuma ʑo pjɤ-nɤ-sɤɣdɯɣ
trs: The elder boy was upset that he did not get the girl.' (140513 shenqi de feitan-zh, 219)

src: nɤʑo ndɤre nɤ-tɯ-ɕɯmtʰu nɯ!
